---
// Privacy Policy (EN) — mirrors /privacidad. Required by Google Play.
import { withBase } from '../../i18n/utils';
import { SITE } from '../../config';
const logo = withBase('/icon.png');
const home = withBase('/en');
const updated = 'June 28, 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Privacy Policy — Ñan Kamay</title>
    <meta name="description" content="How Ñan Kamay collects, uses and protects your data: location, account, media, analytics and live tracking." />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0D1B12" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href={withBase('/favicon.png')} />
    <link rel="alternate" hreflang="es" href={withBase('/privacidad')} />
    <style>
      :root { --night:#0d1b12; --card:#1b4332; --line:#2d6a4f; --accent:#f59e0b; --ink:#fff; --soft:#cfe0d7; --muted:#8fae9e; }
      * { box-sizing:border-box; }
      body { margin:0; background:var(--night); color:var(--ink);
             font-family:system-ui,-apple-system,"Segoe UI",Roboto,sans-serif; line-height:1.6; }
      .wrap { max-width:760px; margin:0 auto; padding:32px 20px 64px; }
      header { display:flex; align-items:center; gap:12px; margin-bottom:8px; }
      header img { width:40px; height:40px; border-radius:10px; }
      header a { color:var(--ink); text-decoration:none; font-weight:800; font-size:18px; }
      h1 { font-size:26px; margin:18px 0 4px; }
      .upd { color:var(--muted); font-size:13px; margin-bottom:8px; }
      h2 { font-size:19px; margin:30px 0 8px; color:#fff; }
      h3 { font-size:15px; margin:18px 0 4px; color:var(--accent); }
      p, li { color:var(--soft); font-size:15px; }
      ul { padding-left:20px; }
      li { margin:5px 0; }
      a { color:var(--accent); }
      .note { background:rgba(27,67,50,.4); border:1px solid var(--line); border-radius:12px; padding:14px 16px; margin:16px 0; }
      .back { display:inline-block; margin-top:28px; color:var(--accent); text-decoration:none; font-weight:700; }
      strong { color:#fff; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="wrap">
      <header>
        <img src={logo} alt="Ñan Kamay" width="40" height="40" />
        <a href={home}>Ñan Kamay</a>
      </header>

      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="upd">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        Ñan Kamay ("the app", "we") is a free app to record hiking and mountain routes. This policy
        explains what data we collect, why, and how you protect and control it. By using the app you
        agree to what is described here.
      </p>

      <div class="note">
        <strong>Summary:</strong> your routes are saved <strong>on your phone first</strong>. They are
        only uploaded to the cloud if you sign in and sync. We never sell your data or use it for ads.
        Usage analytics are anonymous, contain no location, and can be turned off.
      </div>

      <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        Ñan Kamay, developed by Genaro Pretill. Contact:
        <a href={SITE.website} target="_blank" rel="noopener">genaropretill.com</a>
        · <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Data we collect</h2>

      <h3>Account</h3>
      <p>
        If you create an account: your <strong>email address</strong> (or basic Google profile if you
        use "Sign in with Google"). Needed to sync your routes across devices and back them up.
      </p>

      <h3>Location (GPS)</h3>
      <p>
        To record a route we collect your <strong>precise location</strong> while recording, including
        <strong>in the background</strong> (with the screen off) so recording is not interrupted.
        Location is stored on your device and, if you sync, in your account. We do not track your
        location when you are not recording.
      </p>

      <h3>Live tracking (optional)</h3>
      <p>
        If you enable "Share live", your <strong>latest position</strong> is uploaded to our server so
        anyone with your link can see you on a map. The link works via a <strong>temporary capability
        (token)</strong> and the session <strong>expires after 12 hours</strong>, after which it is no
        longer accessible. You decide when to enable it and who you share the link with.
      </p>

      <h3>Waypoint media (optional)</h3>
      <p>
        Photos, videos or voice notes you add to a point of interest are stored on your device and, if
        you sync, in your account. Requires your camera/gallery/microphone permission.
      </p>

      <h3>Trusted contacts (on your phone only)</h3>
      <p>
        Contacts you save for check-in / S.O.S. are stored <strong>only on your device</strong>. They
        are not uploaded to any server. S.O.S. messages are sent via <strong>SMS</strong> from your own
        phone.
      </p>

      <h3>Usage analytics (anonymous)</h3>
      <p>
        To improve the app we log anonymous usage events: which screens are visited (as a pattern, e.g.
        "route detail", never the specific route) and key actions. <strong>We never log your location,
        coordinates or personal data in analytics.</strong> You can <strong>turn it off</strong> in
        Profile → settings.
      </p>

      <h3>Bug reports (optional)</h3>
      <p>
        If you report a problem, we send your message, basic device info (model, Android version, app
        version) and, if you attach one, a screenshot.
      </p>

      <h2>3. How we use the data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Record, display and export your routes (GPX/KML/KMZ).</li>
        <li>Sync and back up your routes if you sign in.</li>
        <li>Enable live tracking when you turn it on.</li>
        <li>Improve stability and experience (anonymous analytics and bug reports).</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not sell your data. We do not use it for advertising or profiling.</p>

      <h2>4. Who we share it with</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Supabase</strong> (database and storage provider): hosts your account, routes, media
          and live sessions when you sync. Data is protected by per-user access rules (RLS).</li>
        <li><strong>Map providers</strong> (OpenStreetMap / Protomaps / Thunderforest): when loading
          online maps, your IP address reaches them as part of the tile request.</li>
        <li><strong>Anyone with your live tracking link</strong>, while the session is active (max 12 h).</li>
        <li><strong>Google Play</strong>: app distribution and basic store diagnostics.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Where it is stored and for how long</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>On your device:</strong> your routes, waypoints and trusted contacts, until you
          delete them or uninstall the app.</li>
        <li><strong>In the cloud (if you sync):</strong> until you delete the route or request account
          deletion.</li>
        <li><strong>Live tracking sessions:</strong> expire automatically after 12 hours.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> anonymous events, kept in aggregate for product analysis.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Your rights and controls</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Delete routes:</strong> remove any route from the app (local and cloud).</li>
        <li><strong>Turn off analytics:</strong> in Profile → settings.</li>
        <li><strong>Stop live:</strong> turn off "Share live" or wait for it to expire.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete your account and data:</strong> email us at <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>
          and we will delete your account and associated data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use encrypted connections (HTTPS), per-user access control in the database, and secure
        credential storage on the device. Access to live tracking requires the exact token and expires
        on its own. No system is 100% foolproof, but we apply reasonable practices to protect you.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children</h2>
      <p>
        The app is not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect data from children
        under that age.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy. We will publish the current version on this page with its update date.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Privacy questions: <a href={SITE.website} target="_blank" rel="noopener">genaropretill.com</a>
        · <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.
      </p>

      <a class="back" href={home}>← Back to home</a>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
